The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal sequence recovery, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents simulation experiments to back up the claims, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of support recovery, which is a common theme in compressed sensing, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing).
